org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.model

Class PackageGenerationParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.model.PackageGenerationParameters

  • public class PackageGenerationParameters
extends Object

    A map of parameters and their values needed in generating a package. This map will need to be populated by the caller of PackageGeneratorService

    The parameters included in this object vary depending on the packaging format selected.

    It is the responsibility of the specific PackageGeneratorImpl to know what parameters it needs to generate a package and retrieve them from this PackageGenerationParameters object.

    • Method Detail

      • addParam

        public void addParam(String key,
                     List<String> values)

        Adds new or updates an entry to the parameters map. If the map previously contained a mapping for the key, the old values will be replaced by the specified values.

        If the specified values include null and/or empty strings, the null and/or empty strings will be removed before the values list is mapped to the key.
        Parameters:
        key - name of a parameter
        values - list of values cannot be null or empty.

      • addParam

        public void addParam(String key,
                     String value)
        Adds new or updates a value to the specified parameter in the map. If a parameter with matching key exists in in the map, new value will be added to the parameter's list of values. If a parameter with matching key does not exist in the map, it will be created and added to the map with the specified value as initial value.
        Parameters:
        key - name of a parameter
        value - Parameter's value cannot be null or empty.

      • removeParam

        public void removeParam(String key)
        Removes a parameter and all of its values from the collection of parameters. If a parameter with matching key does not exist, no operation will be performed.
        Parameters:
        key - name of a parameter to be removed

      • getParam

        public String getParam(String key,
                       int index)

        Returns a single String value at the specified index location in the list of String associated with the given key.

        This is useful in retrieving value for keys that are expected to have only one value.

        Returns null if no parameter exists with matching key.
        Parameters:
        key - The key of the parameter to retrieve.
        index - The index location of the parameter to retrieve
        Returns:
        The string representing the value of the parameter

      • overrideParams

        public void overrideParams(PackageGenerationParameters override)
        Overrides this set of parameters with those in another parameters bundle. Objects in this set that are not in the other set will be left alone. Objects in the other set that are not in this set will be added. Objects in both sets will be changed to the values in the other set.
        Parameters:
        override - The other parameter set to import values for.
